description:
Limited Edition Hardcover with Clamshell Case.

This collector's hardcover is a limited edition of 6,000 units. It comes with a mock poster and a 2 CD set. The hardcover is encased in a clear clamshell. The oversized hardcover is Oversized at the 8¼ x 12 5/8 format. It also includes a 16 page color section that contains all of the covers (including variants). The whole Earth X story is collected in this hardcover, from issues #0, 0.5, 1-12 and X. *NOTE* The Interiors are mostly black and white and the color from the original series is omitted.

This edition is also signed by Alex Ross, Jim Krueger, John Paul Leon and Bill Reinhold

The main series was published by Marvel comics, while this version was published by Graphitti Design.
name: Earth X

description:
Welcome to one of the weirdest titles DC has ever assembled – 6 issues filled with stories of monsters, ghouls and far-out cosmic craziness! 

Each month, you'll be treated to new 10-page chapters in three exciting serials. In this debut issue, Kevin Van Hook and Jerry Ordway bring you the continuing adventures of Lobo, everyone's favorite Czarnian (after all, he's the only one left, so he'd better be your favorite). Aaron Lopresti introduces you to his newest creation, the kind-hearted monster called Garbageman. And Kevin Maguire takes you to the farthest reaches of outer space with the introduction of a hero called Tanga!
name: Weird Worlds
